# Architecture Rule

Use the existing repository architecture as the default source of truth.

- Prefer simple and explicit design.
- Favor composition over inheritance unless local architecture dictates otherwise.
- Keep business logic out of UI, framework glue, transport, and entry layers where practical.
- Reuse existing patterns before inventing new ones.
- Avoid generic dumping grounds like `utils`, `helpers`, or `common` without a real cross-cutting reason.
- Keep modules cohesive and interfaces narrow.
- Do not abstract early; every abstraction must solve a real present problem.
- Prefer extending an existing path over creating a parallel system.
- Keep data flow explicit and side effects visible.
